# Chief Clarity v2 - Windsurf Rules

## Architecture Documentation (MANDATORY)

When adding new functionality, changing architecture, adding new data files, new intents, new modules, or modifying the data flow, you MUST update `docs/new_architecture_typescript.md` to reflect the changes.

What to update:
- New data files: Section 4 (Data File Architecture) + Section 3 (Project Structure)
- New modules: Section 6 (Module Responsibilities)
- New intents: Section 6 (Assembler Context by Intent) + Section 8 (Token Budgets)
- New types: Section 5 (TypeScript Interfaces)
- Architecture decisions: Section 9 (Architecture Decision Record)
- New features: Section 12 (Feature Catalog)
- Changed data flow: Section 6 diagram

Update the doc AFTER code compiles, BEFORE marking the task done.

## README (MANDATORY)

When adding new features, scripts, data files, modules, or changing how to run the app, you MUST update `README.md`.

What to update:
- New features: feature list + relevant section
- New scripts: Scripts table
- New data files: Data Files table
- New modules: Modules table
- Changed structure: project tree
- Changed run commands: Quick Start + Scripts

Update AFTER code works, BEFORE marking the task done.

## Feature Backlog (MANDATORY)

Maintain features in `packages/feature-kit/features/`.
Each feature is a folder (e.g. `FEAT019_Message_queue/`) with a `.json` metadata file and `.md` description.
- New features: create folder + json + md, update `_manifest.json`
- Status changes: update the json file's `status` field through the pipeline:
  `Planned` → `Design Reviewed` → `In Progress` → `Code Reviewed` → `Testing` → `Done` (or `Rejected`)
- Details: edit the `.md` file
- Update when features are discussed, planned, started, or completed.

## App Runs Continuously (CRITICAL)

The app stays open for days. NEVER design features that only trigger on app load/startup/mount.
- Every periodic check must run on a recurring setInterval, not just on mount or tab focus.
- Inbox/nudges: every 2 minutes. State refresh: every 5 minutes.
- All intervals respect loadingRef/inboxProcessingRef guards.
- The headless runner handles background work when the app is closed.

## No Real User Data in Code (CRITICAL)

NEVER include real user data in any committed file. This includes:
- System prompts (`prompts.ts`), LLM instructions, code comments, docs, examples
- Real names (family, contacts, companies), real activities, real locations
- Use generic placeholders: "Task A", "Example Corp", "Child A", "weekly activity"
- Before completing any task, review all modified files for real data leaks.

## Core Rules

- Sacred boundary: TypeScript owns deterministic logic. LLM owns judgment. Neither trespasses.
- Single LLM call per user phrase. No multi-agent pipelines.
- LLM returns structured JSON via tool use only. TypeScript executes.
- Per-intent context assembly. Never send all data to all intents.
- Token budgets enforced by assembler. Lifestyle/profile data is never truncated.
- Atomic file writes via filesystem.ts.
- User timezone from state.userProfile.timezone for all date operations.
- No real user data in code, comments, or examples.
- Chat replies for planning must be 1-2 sentences. Details go in focusBrief write.
